RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 105. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $32,000 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Pr ice $50,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $40,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (Rail at 30 feet).

CLAIM.OWNER: Abbondanza Racing LLC and David A Bernsen LLC

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CASTLE LEOCH reserved in the beginning and moved into the two path, saved ground around the far turn before swing out into approaching the stretch, rallied four deep in the furlong grounds and proved best late. EASTERN OCEAN stalked along the inside, tipped out on the far turn and took aim three wide into the stretch, launched a bid with a furlong left to run, fought between rivals in deep stretch, had the rider lose his crop late and was outkicked by the winner. MARGOT'S BOY set the pace from inside under pressure, headed around the far turn, dueled in stretch and yielded late. FLAVIUS bobbled leaving the gate, went up to press the pace in hand two wide, headed the leader on the far turn, fought through the lead and weakened late. TAISHAN tracked in the three path, went two then three wide around the far turn, got floated out exiting the bend and weakened. LIBERAL (IRE) broke well then settled at the back on the inside, tipped two wide for the far turn, eased further out around the bend then angled five wide into the stretch, offered no response in the lane and walked into the van following the race.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUFF RIDE brushed outer rival at the start, tucked inside at the back into the first turn, moved into range in the middle stages, split foes then tipped out and chased three deep at the quarter pole, took aim three wide into the lane, drew alongside the leader in upper stretch, dueled into the final furlong and edged away in deep stretch. BIG NOVEL prominent early three wide on the first turn then pressed from outside, challenged on the far turn and cleared past the five-sixteenths pole, showed the way two wide into the stretch, met the challenge from RUFF RIDE in upper stretch but yielded in the final sixteenth. TIZZY TWISTER stalked two wide then moved inside on the first turn, shifted back to the two path on the far turn, chased within striking distance through the lane but could not find the needed late kick. RENEGADE PRINCESS tracked four then three wide early, remained wide and came four wide into the stretch and weakened. SWEET HELLO took control from inside then moved into the two path around the clubhouse turn, showed the way with BIG NOVEL alongside up the backstretch, offered no resistance when tested by that rival on the far turn and gave way. FLYMETOTHEMOONBABY brushed leaving the gate, chased three then two wide around the first turn, trailed up the backstretch and through the far turn, eased off the rail leaving that bend to enter the lane three wide and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRIBBAGE BOARD dueled for the lead outside RED FALCON, inched ahead around the bend, cleared with a furlong remaining and held gamely in the end. JOHN DUNBAR broke a hair slow and was coaxed to a forward position from inside, tried to sneak up the rail leaving the turn but lacked room entering the stretch, tipped out at the eighth pole, finished gamely between and got up for second. GRAND TIGER chased two wide into the turn, ridden along while tipping out around the bend, took aim three wide into the stretch, finished willingly down the lane but could not summon the needed final kick. RED FALCON dueled for command from inside, could not keep pace with the leader entering the final furlong, stayed on well from inside but was outkicked for the place and show. BARTON STRONG allowed to settle at the back, advanced four to five wide around the bend but could not find more in the furlong grounds. LOGON TO WIN tracked three wide into the turn, had to alter in from behind BEYOND COMPARE at the five-sixteenths pole, brushed with outer rival at the top of the stretch and failed to rally. KING ZOG settled outside a rival, went four wide into the turn, bumped with BEYOND COMPARE at the quarter pole, steered down to the two path, brushed with LOGON TO WIN at the three-sixteenths pole and could not rally. BEYOND COMPARE forwardly placed early, chased three deep into the turn, shifted in at the five-sixteenths pole, bumped with KING ZOG and checked at the quarter pole and was not persevered with in the lane.

ENTRY.COMMENT: lacked room into str, tipped out, gamely between

SHARED FUTURE up close three deep then shifted into the two path to stalk the pace, traveled between rivals up the backstretch, angled in on the far turn after losing positions and weakened in the lane. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIGNORA MINISTER pressed between rivals to the turn, raced on even terms with UNWRITTEN CODE around the bend and took over at the quarter pole, held a short lead over CRIMSON ROSE through the lane, brushed with that rival outside the sixteenth pole and held gamely to the wire. CRIMSON ROSE pressed the pace three deep, kept the pressure on SIGNORA MINISTER down the lane, brushed that rival at the sixteenth pole and could not get by. PROFESSORS' PRIDE stalked the leaders two wide into the turn, eased out and came four wide into the stretch, kept on through the lane and earned the show honors. UNWRITTEN CODE set the pace inside a pair of rivals, fought with outer pair around the bend, relinquished the lead at the quarter pole, could not kick on with leaders in upper stretch and weakened in the furlong grounds. BELLA RENELLA raced in range early, traveled three wide into the turn, spun five wide off the bend and weakened.
